{
  "texts": [
    "In Fig. 6, circles are nodes, and empty boxes show aggregation of neighbor/adjacent nodes.",
    "The model aggregates messages from A's local graph neighbors (i.e., B, C, and D).",
    "In turn, the messages coming from neighbors are based on information aggregated from their respective neighborhoods, and so on.",
    "This visualization shows a two-layer version of a message-passing model.",
    "Notice that the computation graph of the GNN forms a tree structure by unfolding the neighborhood around the target node [17]."
  ]
}